place it had good functionality was in an area I didn't care about (caching proxy).<br>
<br>
On the recommendation of some folks over at JustLinux, I downloaded IPcop and installed it.  It's a &quot;fork&quot; of the Smoothwall tree, but it's under constant development (unlike GPL Smoothwall, which is the bastard child of a commercial product).<br>
<br>
I'm slight more impressed with IPcop, since it will allow me to define multiple external IP addresses.  Unfortunately I cannot do static NAT.<br>
<br>
I'm fairly disappointed with my experience in specialized firewall distributions.  I think I might eventually end up just writing my own firewall from scratch with iptables.  If you want something done right, do it yourself I guess <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><br>
