<br>
Complex iptables NAT scripts can start to look like <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.linuxguruz.com/iptables/scripts/rc.firewall_023.txt">this one</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->(which I based my script off of), and being able to administer multiple rules more easily is a huge plus IMO :&gt; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=chortnazgul>chort nazgul</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist</span><br>  Posts: 891<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/26/03 8:37 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: [Networking] If you're looking at Smoothwall, don't both</span><hr size=1> Well now I'm much happier.  I found out that it's possible to manually define your own iptables rules and import them into IPcop, so I guess I get the best of both worlds.  <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.ipcop.org/cgi-bin/twiki/view/IPCop/IPCopAddons">Details here</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
I think I have fwbuilder on my Mandrake box.  I'll have to look into that a bit more.  I fiddled with some graphical builder tool when I first installed Mandrake, but since I already had a gateway firewall I didn't actually apply rules to my server interfaces.  Food for thought.<br>
<br>
I'm going to investigate the iptables syntax more closely now that I have my IPcop firewall setup the way I want it (to the extent the admin interface will allow).  Due to my work I get quite a bit of &quot;shoulder surfing&quot; experience with PIX and I'm getting fairly proficient in the syntax.  I actually perfer it to the CheckPoint method of defining a bunch of groups, then compiling, then installing, blah, blah, etc.  All that clicking is a PITA when you could just write a one-liner and have it take effect immediately. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm59.showPrevMessage?topicID=2230.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm59.showNextMessage?topicID=2230.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm59.emailToFriend?topicID=2230.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm59.threadControl?topicID=2230.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm59.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=2230.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm59.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=2230.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/unsubscribe.gif width=20 heigh